obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE IMPROVEMENTS IN TOWNS ACT, 1850`
  line `A CT N O. XXVI OF 18 5 0`
  line `[ Passed on the 21 st June, 1850.]`
  line `1. Repeals. Act 10, 1842.`
  line `2. Act may be put in force by order of Local Government wherever inhabitants desire it.`
  line `3, 4. Notice of application to Government to be advertised in order that inhabitants may declare their`
  line `wishes, and (4) decision of Local Government herein to be final.`
  line `5. Act to come in force from publication of order, and order to be conclusive, & c.`
  line `6, 7. Commission formed of Magistrate and inhabitant s to be appointed by Government, who shall`
  line `make rules, & c. for furtherance of Act: and (7) the rules shall be for objects in Act specified.`
  line `8. Empowers Commissioners to make necessary contracts and apply the taxes.`
  line `9. Commissioners not to be personally l aible on contracts but only for misapplication of monies and`
  line `gross neglect.`
  line `10. Act 10, 1839, for recovery of fines to apply to taxes, & c. under this Act.`
  line `11. No rate or assessment to be invalid for defect of form, & c.`
  line `12. All moveable property on the assessed premises to be liable for taxes.`
  line `13. Account of receipts and disbursements to be submitted annually to Local Government.`
  line `14. Empowers Government to suspend the operation of the Act.`
  line `An Act to enable improvements to be made in Towns.`
  line `Whereas Act X. 1842, was passed for enabling the inhabitants of any place of public resort or residence,`
  line `under the Presidency of Fort William, not within the Town of Calcutta, to make better provision for`
  line `purposes connected with public health and convenien ce, but the said Act has proved ineffectual for the`
  line `purpose, and it is expedient to amend the provisions thereof, and to extend the like powers to the inhabitants`
  line `of Town in the other Presidencies under the Government of the East india Company, It is enact ed as follows:`
  line `I. Act X. 1842, is repealed.`
  line `II. If it shall appear to the Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant Governor, of any Presidency`
  line `or Place within the Territories under the Government of the East India Company, that the inhabitants of any`
  line `Town or Suburb, not within the Town of Calcutta, Madras, or Bombay, are desirous of making better`
  line `provision for making, repairing, cleaning, lighting, or watching any public streets, roads, drains, or tanks,`
  line `or for the prevention of nuisances, or for impr oving the said Town or Suburb in any other manner, the said`
  line `Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant Governor, may order this Act to be put in force within`
  line `such Town or Suburb.`
  line `III. Whenever any application shall be made to the Government for putting this Act in force in any`
  line `Town or Suburb, notice thereof shall be given in the Government Gazette of the P residency, or place, and`
  line `also by proclamation within such Town or Suburb, setting forth the purposes of the application, and giving`
  line `reasonable time fo r all inhabitants of such Town or Suburb, who are minded to declare themselves for or`
  line `against the adoption of this Act therein, for such purposes or any of them.`
  line `IV. The Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant Governor, shall take all such declarations into`
  line `due consideration, and after the time allowed for receiving the same, shall make a final order, which shall`
  line `be published in the Govern ment Gazette, and also notified by proclamation within such Town or Suburb,`
  line `to the effect that the application appears, or does not appear, to be according to the wishes of the inhabitants,`
  line `either wholly, or in respect to one or more of the purposes in respect of which it is ma de; and if the whole`
  line `or any part of it shall appear to be according to the wishes of the inhabitants, then that this Act shall be`
  line `thenceforth in force in such town or Suburb, for such purposes only as shall be mentioned in the Order.`
  line `V. Whenever any such order shall order shall be made and published as aforesaid, this Act shall come`
  line `into force within the said Town or Suburb, for such purposes as are mentioned in the Order, and the making`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-2
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Page 2`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `and publication of the said Order shall be conclusive evidence that t he provisions of this Act have been`
  line `complied with, and that it is thenceforth in force within the said Town or Suburb, for such purposes as are`
  line `mentioned in the Order.`
  line `VI. Whenever this Act shall come into force in any Town or Suburb, the Governor or Gover nor in`
  line `Council, or Lieutenant Governor, shall appoint the Magistrate and such number of the inhabitants thereof`
  line `as to him shall appear necessary, to be Commissioners for putting the Act in force, and shall give authority`
  line `to them to prepare Rules for more e ffectually accomplishing the purposes for which they are appointed;`
  line `which Rules, when approved by the Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant Governors, shall be`
  line `of the same force within the said Town or Suburb, until altered or rescinded as hereina fter provided, as if`
  line `they were inserted in this Act. And the said Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant Governor, may`
  line `remove any of the Commissioners and appoint others, and may fill up vacancies occurring among the`
  line `Commissioners in such manner as may seem to him fit.`
  line `VII. The Rules to be prepared by the said Commissioners shall provide, among other things, for those`
  line `following, that is to say:`
  line `1. The appointment and management of all necessary Officers and Servants of the Commissioners, and`
  line `the sal aries to be allowed to them.`
  line `2. The definition of the persons of property within the Town or Suburb to be taxed for raising the monies`
  line `necessary for the purpose of this Act, whether by House Assessment or Town Duties, or otherwise, the`
  line `amount or rate of th e taxes to be imposed, the manner of raising and collecting them, and ensuring the`
  line `safety and due application of them when collected.`
  line `3. The manner in which from time to time the Rules in force are to be amended or rescinded, and new`
  line `Rules are to be made, with the approval in every case of the Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant`
  line Governor.
  line `4. The definition and prohibition of nuisances within the Town or Sub urb.`
  line `5. The imposition of reasonable penalties for breach of any Rule made by the Commissioners, not`
  line `exceeding Fifty Rupees, or in the case of continuing nuisance, not exceeding Five Rupees for every day`
  line `that such nuisance is continued.`
  line `VIII. The Commissioners appointed fr o m time to time shall have full power to make all necessary`
  line `contr acts, for the purposes of this Act, and apply the taxes raised as aforesaid in the necessary works, and`
  line `in payment of their Officers and Servants, and in the other expenses incident to the execution of this Act`
  line `within the said Town or Suburb.`
  line `IX. No Commis sioner shall be personally liable for any contract made by the Commissioners on behalf`
  line `of the inhabitants of such Town or Suburb; but every Commissioner shall be laible for any misapplication`
  line `of the monies collected, to which he shall have been knowingly party or privy, or which shall have happened`
  line `through gross neglect of his duty and shall be liable to be sued for the same as for money due to, and the`
  line `suit of the East india Company.`
  line `X. The powers of Act II. 1839, for the recovery of fines, shall be appl ied for the recovery of all arrears`
  line `of taxes and penalties under this Act; and every Magistrate shall put in force the powers of the said Act II.`
  line `1839 for that purpose, whenever thereunto required by the Commissioners, or any of their Officers deputed`
  line `by them for the purposes of enforcing payment of arrears of taxed imposed under this Act.`
  line `XI. No rate on property made under this Act shall be invalid for defect of form: and it shall be enough`
  line `in any such rate on property, or any Assessment of value for the purpose of making such rate, if the property`
  line `rated or assessed shall be so described as to be generally known; and it shall not be necessary to name the`
  line `owner or occupier thereof.`
  line `XII. All moveable property found in any house or building or upon any land assessed under this Act`
  line `may be seized and sold by warrant of a Magistrate for payment of any arrear of tax laid on such house,`
  line `building or land under this Act.`
  line `XIII. All Commissioners acting in execution of this Act shall, on or before the last day of Apr il in every`
  line `year, make up and send to the Governor or Governor in Council, or Lieutenant Governor, an account of all`
  line `works executed by them, and of all sums received and spent by them in the foregoing year, in such form`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
